{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DZNzxGSmzFzZqrXhVApCCS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Python Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-04-24\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public Python surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/python/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Python Interface\n11\t\n12\tThis file owns Python-visible symbol spelling and attribute casing.\n13\tCross-binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n14\t\n15\t## Runtime surface\n16\t\n17\tThe canonical runtime verbs available to Python callers are:\n18\t\n19\t- `Engine.open(...)`\n20\t- `engine.write(...)`\n21\t- `engine.search(...)`\n22\t- `engine.close()`\n23\t- `admin.configure(...)`\n24\t\n25\t`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\n26\towned by `design/engine.md`.\n27\t\n28\t`Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` accepts the\n29\tengine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in snake_case:\n30\t\n31\t- `embedder_pool_size`\n32\t- `scheduler_runtime_threads`\n33\t- `provenance_row_cap`\n34\t- `embedder_call_timeout_ms`\n35\t- `slow_threshold_ms`\n36\t\n37\tThe keyword form and `EngineConfig` object form are equivalent. Python\n38\texecutor usage remains caller-owned and is not an engine config field.\n39\t\n40\t## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n41\t\n42\tThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n43\t\n44\t- `engine.drain(timeout_s=...)`\n45\t- `engine.counters()`\n46\t- `engine.set_profiling(enabled=...)`\n47\t- `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(value=...)`\n48\t\n49\tSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n50\t\n51\t- `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`\n52\t\n53\tThe helper maps engine events into Python `logging.LogRecord`s with the stable\n54\t`fathomdb` payload described by `design/bindings.md`.\n55\t\n56\t## Caller-visible data shapes\n57\t\n58\t- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n59\t- `SearchResult.projection_cursor`\n60\t- `SearchResult.soft_fallback.branch`\n61\t\n62\t`soft_fallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n63\t\n64\t## Errors\n65\t\n66\tPython exposes one catch-all base class plus one concrete subclass per canonical\n67\trow in `design/errors.md`.\n68\t\n69\tExamples of caller-visible subclasses:\n70\t\n71\t- `DatabaseLockedError`\n72\t- `CorruptionError`\n73\t- `MigrationError`\n74\t- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n75\t- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n76\t- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n77\t- `SchemaValidationError`\n78\t- `OverloadedError`\n79\t- `ClosingError`\n80\t\n81\tPayload fields remain typed attributes; callers do not dispatch on message\n82\ttext.\n83\t\n84\t## Non-presence\n85\t\n86\tPython does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\n87\tthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `check-integrity`, `--quick`,\n88\t`--full`, or `--round-trip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n89\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"832e6e92-5689-410c-95d4-734b1bf78ed2","uuid":"3d73cd6c-a286-43ac-aa8a-2ad5369cae56","timestamp":"2026-05-16T17:49:06.126Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/dev/interfaces/python.md","content":"---\ntitle: Python Public Interface\ndate: 2026-04-24\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public Python surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/python/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Python Interface\n\nThis file owns Python-visible symbol spelling and attribute casing.\nCross-binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Runtime surface\n\nThe canonical runtime verbs available to Python callers are:\n\n- `Engine.open(...)`\n- `engine.write(...)`\n- `engine.search(...)`\n- `engine.close()`\n- `admin.configure(...)`\n\n`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\nowned by `design/engine.md`.\n\n`Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` accepts the\nengine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in snake_case:\n\n- `embedder_pool_size`\n- `scheduler_runtime_threads`\n- `provenance_row_cap`\n- `embedder_call_timeout_ms`\n- `slow_threshold_ms`\n\nThe keyword form and `EngineConfig` object form are equivalent. Python\nexecutor usage remains caller-owned and is not an engine config field.\n\n## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n\nThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n\n- `engine.drain(timeout_s=...)`\n- `engine.counters()`\n- `engine.set_profiling(enabled=...)`\n- `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(value=...)`\n\nSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n\n- `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`\n\nThe helper maps engine events into Python `logging.LogRecord`s with the stable\n`fathomdb` payload described by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Caller-visible data shapes\n\n- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n- `SearchResult.projection_cursor`\n- `SearchResult.soft_fallback.branch`\n\n`soft_fallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n\n## Errors\n\nPython exposes one catch-all base class plus one concrete subclass per canonical\nrow in `design/errors.md`.\n\nExamples of caller-visible subclasses:\n\n- `DatabaseLockedError`\n- `CorruptionError`\n- `MigrationError`\n- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n- `SchemaValidationError`\n- `OverloadedError`\n- `ClosingError`\n\nPayload fields remain typed attributes; callers do not dispatch on message\ntext.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nPython does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\nthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `check-integrity`, `--quick`,\n`--full`, or `--round-trip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
